DESCRIPTION:
This S&W model 686 (AKA: "Distinguished Combat Magnum") is one of the last group of .357 magnum, 4" barrel, service revolvers purchased by the Kentucky State Police for issue to State Capitol Officers.  It has a KSP property number engraved on the left side, plus bears the original Hogue Monogrips.  Additionally, it has a white outline adjustable rear sight and red ramp front sight.  This weapon comes in a S&W hard case, with six Safariland Speed-Loaders, a KSP issue black retention holster, and one box of factory .357 Magnum 158 grain, SJSP ammunition.

HISTORY:
A couple years after it was placed in servcie, this meticulously maintained service weapon was purchased by the Officer who carried it, when KSP replaced their EDC S&W revolvers with Glock 35 semi-auto pistols.  As such, this revolver shows almost no carry wear and has a very low round count through it.

If you are looking for a great shooting, professionally maintained, totally reliable .357 Magnum stainless steel revolver, at a fair price, this is it.

For Sale:  7N1 Soviet Match Grade Sniper Ammo 7.62X54R
location: Torrance, South Bay LA, Los Angeles, California
postcontent:
Unopened 440 round tin of 7N1 Soviet ammo.

For local face-to-face sale only in the Redondo beach and adjacent South Bay L.A. 
areas (Hawthorne, Manhattan Beach, Torrance ...)  

7N1 Soviet/Russian sniper ammo is one of the most sought after rounds by 7.62X54R  shooters.  Check out the auction sites and see what it's going for.

Russian 1997 7.62x54R 152 grain "7N1" CHAnNEPCKnE Sniper ammunition was developed by Russian armorer Sabelnikov for the SVD “Snayperskaya Vintovka Dragunova” which translates as (Yevgeniy) Dragunov's Sniper Rifle.
   The match grade cartridge consists of an annealed copper washed steel cases with a special 15 grain boat tail bullet. It has a steel jacketed projectile with an air pocket, steel core, and a lead knocker in the base which is designed to cause the projectile to "tumble" once it hits its target. 

Though made for the Dragunov, this ammo should be fine in any 7.62x54R Mosin rifle, like the Dragunov Tiger Carbine, M91, M38, M44, 91/30, PSL, SVT, Finnish M39 Chinese Type 53, (and NDM-86/EM-351, when chambered in 54R) ...   
Headstamp is 188 (Novosibirsk Factory) over 97.  

 I've had emails from out-of-state buyers, thanks, but I'm not shipping on this item.  FTF only.  Must be 18 or over to purchase.

440 rd tin, $450

Thanks for looking.
